-- >> source: Karachi street-food classic
>> servings: 4
>> time: 5 hours (including marination)
-- >> description: Smoky, spice-crusted leg quarters with skin on — adapted for grill or oven.

-- =========================
-- SCORE & SALT THE CHICKEN
-- =========================

Make 3-4 deep slashes through the skin and into the meat on each @chicken leg quarters (skin on){4} going down to the bone. Rub @salt{1%tbsp} into the cuts and all over the surface.

-- =================
-- MAKE THE MARINADE
-- =================

In a large bowl, combine @plain yogurt{200%g}, @lemon juice{3%tbsp}, @garlic cloves, grated{6}, @ginger, grated{1%tbsp}, @Kashmiri red chili powder{1.5%tbsp}, @cumin powder{1%tsp}, @coriander powder{1%tsp}, @garam masala{1%tsp}, @turmeric{0.5%tsp}, @black pepper, coarsely ground{0.5%tsp}, @mustard oil{2%tbsp}, and @raw papaya paste{1%tbsp}. Mix until smooth.

-- Papaya alternatives: use @pineapple juice{2%tbsp} or half a small @kiwi, mashed{1} instead of papaya paste. Don't marinate longer than overnight with either substitute.

-- ====================
-- MARINATE THE CHICKEN
-- ====================

Add the scored leg quarters to the marinade and coat thoroughly, pressing the paste into every slash. Cover and refrigerate for ~{4%hours} up to overnight.

Remove from the fridge ~{30%minutes} before cooking so the chicken comes to room temperature.

-- ===========================
-- METHOD 1: GRILLING
-- ===========================

Set the grill on high and let it get up to heat. Place the leg quarters skin-side down and grill until skin is charred and crisp, about ~{7%minutes}. Watch for flare-ups.

Reduce flame to low / medium and flip chicken to non-skin side. Close the lid and cook until internal temperature at the thickest part of the thigh reaches 74°C / 165°F, roughly ~{25%minutes} more.

-- ===========================
-- METHOD 2: OVEN ROASTING
-- ===========================

-- Preheat oven to 220°C / 425°F. Place marinated leg quarters skin-side up on a #wire rack{} set over a #sheet pan{}.

-- Bake for ~{40%minutes} until internal temp hits 74°C / 165°F.

-- Switch to broil on high for ~{5%minutes} to blister and crisp the skin. Watch closely to avoid burning.

-- =================
-- REST & SERVE
-- =================

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Sprinkle generously with @chaat masala{1%tsp}, squeeze @fresh lemon wedges{4} over the top, and serve on a bed of @sliced onion rings{1} with @fresh green chilies{4} on the side. A warm naan and raita complete the plate.
